                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote scope="major" xml:id="hand-1">
                                <p>The <locus from="1r" to="1r">recto</locus> was copied by Hand A
                                    in a <term type="script">slanted ogival majuscule</term> script
                                    in black ink, with breathings and accents, and flourishing of
                                    tails into the lower margin.</p>
                                <p>The horizontal stroke for <hi rend="italic">nu</hi> is present,
                                    joined with a downward stroke to the right. Mute <hi rend="italic">iota</hi> is absent. Grave accents are usually
                                    almost horizontal. <foreign xml:lang="la">Nomina sacra</foreign>
                                    are unaccentuated. <foreign xml:lang="la">Nomina sacra</foreign>
                                    strokes are ornamented with vertical bars. </p>
                                <p>The ligatures ΑΥ and ΟΥ are present.</p>
                                <p>Punctuation used includes the lower and upper points and the
                                    lower and middle commas.</p>
                            </handNote>

                            <handNote scope="major" xml:id="hand-2">
                                <p>The <locus from="1v" to="1v">verso</locus> was copied by Hand B
                                    in an upright <term type="script">St Neilos style mixed
                                        minuscule</term> script, in brown ink. There is little
                                    variation in letter size, and slight flourishing of tails into
                                    the lower margin.</p>
                                <p>Syllabic abbreviations are not used, apart from the horizontal
                                    stroke for <hi rend="italic">nu</hi>,which can appear in
                                    mid-line, and there are no superscript word endings. Breathings
                                    are both angular and round, and mute <hi rend="italic">iota</hi>
                                    is absent. <foreign xml:lang="la">Nomina sacra</foreign> are
                                    accentuated only when more than three letters long. <foreign xml:lang="la">Nomina sacra</foreign> strokes are ornamented
                                    with pairs of vertical bars. The double dot is only used
                                    erroneously, on diphthongs (<locus from="1v" to="1v">verso,
                                        col. b, lines 29, 31</locus>). Circumflexes sometimes appear
                                    above breathings, but are not markedly enlarged.</p>
                                <p>Majuscule forms of <hi rend="italic">epsilon</hi>, <hi rend="italic">kappa</hi>, <hi rend="italic">lambda</hi>, <hi rend="italic">pi</hi> and <hi rend="italic">sigma</hi> are
                                    present.</p>
                                <p>Punctuation used includes the lower, middle and upper points and
                                    lower comma.</p>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>

